So, since I happen to be interested in peacebuilding in institutes and groups where conflict is an issue, I’ve been thinking about what peacebuilding measures are needed for the great fundraising week ahead of us.

Maybe you too are wondering, thinking or have already endorsed the call: Let’s organise the Malteser Dinner 2015 in full respect of the rotating chair government and in joint effort with the Malteser European Group, the Mouvement des Cadets de l’Europe and many more enthropobalist organisations,

as they can say very shortly and concisely J “The Association of the European Malteser Movements with its organically joined European and National Youth Groups implements in Europe an important, European and intra-European contribution to “EaP” (European Alliance for Peace) in the aspired objectives of ACTION (cooperation) for Europe and intra-European peace.” ;

You can read further information about the donation model of the Malteser in transfomration of donation into peacebuilding into Melting Pole Week 2015 and the declaration of the Malteser (in German with translation) on Moments of Contemporary History.
